# Load necessary libraries
library(readxl)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(openxlsx)
library(extrafont)

# Load fonts for Windows device
loadfonts(device = "win")
#fonts()

# Load the data from the Excel file
file_path <- "Paper 2- Group 1 (1).xlsx"
sheet_names <- c("Mass (0.48ng)", "Mass (1.92ng)", "Mass(14.754ng)", "Mass(22.131ng)", "Mass (29.508ng)")

# Read the data from each sheet
data_list <- lapply(sheet_names, function(sheet) {
  read.xlsx(file_path, sheet = sheet, colNames = TRUE)
})

# Name the data frames in the list
names(data_list) <- sheet_names

# Combine all data into one dataframe with an additional column for DNA mass
combined_data <- bind_rows(
  lapply(names(data_list), function(name) {
    df <- data_list[[name]]
    df$Mass <- name
    df
  })
)

# Convert the Mass column to a factor with ordered levels
combined_data$Mass <- factor(combined_data$Mass, levels = sheet_names, ordered = TRUE)

# Calculate the difference ( = Control - Exp) for each replication
combined_data <- combined_data %>%
  mutate(
    Delta_1 = Control_Replication.1 - Exp_Replication.1,
    Delta_2 = Control_Replication.2 - Exp_Replication.2,
    Delta_3 = Control_Replication.3 - Exp_Replication.3
  )

# Gather the Delta columns into a long format
delta_data <- combined_data %>%
  select(Mass, Drain.Voltage, starts_with("Delta")) %>%
  gather(key = "Replication", value = "Delta", Delta_1:Delta_3)

# Plot the differences with jittered points for grading
p <- ggplot(delta_data, aes(x = Mass, y = Delta)) +
  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape = NA, fill = NA) +
  geom_jitter(aes(color = Drain.Voltage), size = 1.5, width = 0.2) +
  labs(
    x = "DNA Mass (ng)",
    y = expression(Differential~Current~(mu*A))
  ) +
  scale_color_gradient(low = "#B8860B", high = "navyblue") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    axis.text = element_text(size = 12, family = "Times New Roman"),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 12, family = "Times New Roman"),
    legend.text = element_text(size = 12, family = "Times New Roman"),
    legend.title = element_text(size = 12, family = "Times New Roman"),
    legend.position = c(0.2, 0.7),  # Position legend in bottom right inside plot
    legend.direction = "vertical",  # Arrange legend items vertically
    panel.background = element_blank(), # Set the background color to white
    plot.background = element_blank(), # Set the plot background color to white
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(), # Set the major grid lines to white
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
    panel.border = element_rect(color = "black", fill = NA),
  ) +
  scale_x_discrete(labels = c("0.48", "1.92", "14.754", "22.131", "29.508"))

# Save the plot
ggsave("delta_plot_with_all_voltage_values_graded_no_legend.png", plot = p, width = 10, height = 6, dpi = 300)

# Display the plot
print(p)

# Load fonts for Windows device
loadfonts(device = "win")
#fonts()

# Load the data from the Excel file
file_path <- "Paper 2- Group 1 (1).xlsx"
sheet_names <- c("Mass (0.48ng)", "Mass (1.92ng)", "Mass(14.754ng)", "Mass(22.131ng)", "Mass (29.508ng)")

# Read the data from each sheet
data_list <- lapply(sheet_names, function(sheet) {
  read.xlsx(file_path, sheet = sheet, colNames = TRUE)
})

# Name the data frames in the list
names(data_list) <- sheet_names

# Combine all data into one dataframe with an additional column for DNA mass
combined_data <- bind_rows(
  lapply(names(data_list), function(name) {
    df <- data_list[[name]]
    df$Mass <- name
    df
  })
)

# Convert the Mass column to a factor with ordered levels
combined_data$Mass <- factor(combined_data$Mass, levels = sheet_names, ordered = TRUE)

# Calculate the difference ( = Control - Exp) for each replication
combined_data <- combined_data %>%
  mutate(
    Delta_1 = Control_Replication.1 - Exp_Replication.1,
    Delta_2 = Control_Replication.2 - Exp_Replication.2,
    Delta_3 = Control_Replication.3 - Exp_Replication.3
  )

# Gather the Delta columns into a long format
delta_data <- combined_data %>%
  select(Mass, Drain.Voltage, starts_with("Delta")) %>%
  gather(key = "Replication", value = "Delta", Delta_1:Delta_3)

# Function to calculate the pairwise distance between distributions
calculate_pairwise_distance <- function(data, mass_levels) {
  results <- data.frame()
  
  for (voltage in unique(data$Drain.Voltage)) {
    sub_data <- data %>% filter(Drain.Voltage == voltage)
    
    if (nrow(sub_data) == 0) next
    
    # Calculate pairwise distances for each mass level combination
    for (i in 1:(length(mass_levels) - 1)) {
      for (j in (i + 1):length(mass_levels)) {
        mass1 <- mass_levels[i]
        mass2 <- mass_levels[j]
        
        if (nrow(sub_data %>% filter(Mass == mass1)) == 0 || nrow(sub_data %>% filter(Mass == mass2)) == 0) {
          dist_value <- NA
        } else {
          dist_value <- abs(
            median(sub_data$Delta[sub_data$Mass == mass1], na.rm = TRUE) - 
              median(sub_data$Delta[sub_data$Mass == mass2], na.rm = TRUE)
          )
        }
        
        results <- rbind(
          results,
          data.frame(
            Drain.Voltage = voltage,
            Mass1 = mass1,
            Mass2 = mass2,
            Distance = dist_value
          )
        )
      }
    }
  }
  
  return(results)
}

# Calculate pairwise distances
mass_levels <- c("Mass (0.48ng)", "Mass (1.92ng)", "Mass(14.754ng)", "Mass(22.131ng)", "Mass (29.508ng)")
pairwise_distances <- calculate_pairwise_distance(delta_data, mass_levels)


# Add a unique Mass_Comparison label for each mass pair comparison and ensure the order is correct (small to large)
pairwise_distances <- pairwise_distances %>%
  mutate(
    Mass_Comparison = factor(
      paste(Mass1, "-", Mass2),
      levels = unique(paste(Mass1, "-", Mass2))[order(as.numeric(gsub("[^0-9.]", "", Mass1)),
                                                      as.numeric(gsub("[^0-9.]", "", Mass2)))]
    )
  )

# Define a gradient color palette from light to bold
color_palette <- colorRampPalette(c("navyblue", "#B8860B"))

p = ggplot(pairwise_distances, aes(x = as.factor(Drain.Voltage), y = Distance)) +
  geom_boxplot(color = "black", fill = NA) + # Boxplot with black outline
  geom_jitter(aes(color = Mass_Comparison), size = 2) + # Jitter points with color based on Mass comparison
  scale_color_manual(values = color_palette(length(unique(pairwise_distances$Mass_Comparison))), 
                     name = "Mass Pair Comparison") + # Gradient color palette
  labs(x = "Drain Voltage", y = "Mass-Change Differential Current") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(size = 12, family = "Times New Roman"),
    axis.text.y =  element_text(size = 12, family = "Times New Roman"),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 12, family = "Times New Roman"),
    legend.text = element_text(size = 12, family = "Times New Roman"),
    legend.position = c(0.85, 0.8),  # Position legend in bottom right inside plot
    legend.direction = "vertical",  # Arrange legend items vertically
    legend.spacing.y = unit(1, 'cm'),  # Further reduce space between legend lines
    legend.key.size = unit(0.8, 'lines'),  # Reduce the size of the legend key
    legend.title = element_blank(),
    panel.background = element_blank(), # Set the background color to white
    plot.background = element_blank(), # Set the plot background color to white
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(), # Remove major grid lines
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
    panel.border = element_rect(color = "black", fill = NA) # Add black border
  )
ggsave("Differential.png", plot = p, width = 10, height = 6)
 knitr::include_graphics("Differential.png")

1.6 Figure4(F)

rm(list = ls())
library(readxl)
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
library(extrafont)
library(caret)
library(scales)
library(broom)
library(purrr)
library(pracma)
library(minpack.lm)
# Load fonts for Windows device
loadfonts(device = "win")

# Load data from the Excel file
file_path <- "Paper 2- Group 1 (1).xlsx"

# Read each sheet
data_mass_14_754 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass(14.754ng)")
data_mass_22_131 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass(22.131ng)")
data_mass_29_508 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass (29.508ng)")
data_mass_0_48 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass (0.48ng)")
data_mass_1_92 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass (1.92ng)")

# Add a column for the mass value to each dataset
data_mass_14_754$Mass <- 14.754
data_mass_22_131$Mass <- 22.131
data_mass_29_508$Mass <- 29.508
data_mass_0_48$Mass <- 0.48
data_mass_1_92$Mass <- 1.92


# Combine training and test datasets
combined_data <- bind_rows(data_mass_14_754, data_mass_22_131, data_mass_29_508, data_mass_0_48, data_mass_1_92)

# Prepare training and test datasets
train_data <- combined_data %>%
  rename(DrainVoltage = `Drain Voltage`)


train_data_filtered <- train_data %>%
  filter(DrainVoltage %in% c(-4, -3, -2))

train_data_filtered <- train_data_filtered %>%
  mutate(diff1 = Control_Replication.1 - Exp_Replication.1,
         diff2 = Control_Replication.2 - Exp_Replication.2,
         diff3 = Control_Replication.3 - Exp_Replication.3)


jitter_data <- train_data_filtered %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(diff1, diff2, diff3), names_to = "Replication", values_to = "Difference")


mean_sd_data <- train_data_filtered %>%
  group_by(Mass, DrainVoltage) %>%
  summarize(
    mean_diff = mean(c(diff1, diff2, diff3), na.rm = TRUE),
    SD_diff = sd(c(diff1, diff2, diff3), na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  distinct(Mass, DrainVoltage, mean_diff, SD_diff)


# Initialize RMSE results table
rmse_results <- tibble(
  DrainVoltage = numeric(),
  Model = character(),
  Dataset = character(),
  RMSE = numeric(),
  Normalized_RMSE = numeric()
)

target_voltages <- c(-4, -3, -2)

mean_sd_data_filtered <- mean_sd_data %>% filter(DrainVoltage %in% target_voltages)

# Initialize a list to store equations
equations <- tibble(
  DrainVoltage = numeric(),
  equation = character()
)

# Iterate over each target voltage to fit models and extract coefficients
for (voltage in target_voltages) {
  # Filter train data for the current voltage
  train_data <- mean_sd_data_filtered %>% filter(DrainVoltage == voltage)
  
  # Fit the linear model for the current voltage
  linear_fit <- lm(mean_diff ~ Mass, data = train_data)
  
  # Extract the coefficients (intercept and slope)
  intercept <- coef(linear_fit)[1]
  slope <- coef(linear_fit)[2]
  
  # Create an equation label
  equation_label <- paste("y = ", round(intercept, 2), " + ", round(slope, 2), "x")
  
  # Store the equation in the equations table
  equations <- equations %>%
    add_row(DrainVoltage = voltage, equation = equation_label)
}

print(equations)
## # A tibble: 3  2
##   DrainVoltage equation              
##          <dbl> <chr>                 
## 1           -4 y =  4.72  +  24.71 x 
## 2           -3 y =  30.91  +  13.63 x
## 3           -2 y =  42.1  +  5.88 x
# Iterate through each target voltage
for (voltage in target_voltages) {
  # Filter train and test data for the current voltage
  train_data <- mean_sd_data_filtered %>% filter(DrainVoltage == voltage)
  
  # Linear Model Predictions
  linear_fit <- lm(mean_diff ~ Mass, data = train_data)
  train_pred_linear <- predict(linear_fit, newdata = train_data)
 
  
  # Compute RMSE for Linear Model
  rmse_train_linear <- sqrt(mean((train_pred_linear - train_data$mean_diff)^2))
 
  
  # Normalized RMSE
  norm_rmse_train_linear <- (rmse_train_linear / mean(train_data$mean_diff)) * 100

  
  # Append results to RMSE results table
  rmse_results <- rmse_results %>%
    add_row(DrainVoltage = voltage, Model = "Linear", Dataset = "Train", RMSE = rmse_train_linear, Normalized_RMSE = norm_rmse_train_linear) 
}



custom_trans <- trans_new(
  "custom",
  transform = function(x) {
    ifelse(
      x >= 0.48 & x <= 1.92, (x - 0.48) * 2 + 0.48,
      ifelse(
        x >= 7.77 & x <= 9.71, (x - 7.77) * 1.1 + 7.77,
        x
      )
    )
  },
  inverse = function(x) {
    ifelse(
      x >= 0.48 & x <= 1.92, (x - 0.48) / 2 + 0.48,
      ifelse(
        x >= 7.77 & x <= 9.71, (x - 7.77) / 1.1 + 7.77,
        x
      )
    )
  }
)

ggplot() +
  # Jittered points for individual differences (Training Data) without legend
  geom_jitter(data = jitter_data, aes(x = Mass, y = Difference, color = DrainVoltage),

  geom_point(data = mean_sd_data, aes(x = Mass, y = mean_diff, color = DrainVoltage, shape = "Train Points"), 
             size = 3, stroke = 1.5) +
  
  # Regression lines for each voltage using training data
  geom_smooth(data = mean_sd_data, aes(x = Mass, y = mean_diff, group = DrainVoltage, linetype = "Fitted Model"), 
              method = "lm", se = FALSE, color = "gray") +
  
  # Define linetype mappings
  scale_linetype_manual(
    name = "Line Type",
    values = c("Fitted Model" = "dashed"),
    guide = NULL
  ) +
  
  # Labels and title

    y = expression(Differential~Current~(mu*A)),  # \mu in y-axis title
    color = "Drain Voltage",
    shape = "Data Type"
  ) +
  
  # Formatting the plot
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    axis.text = element_text(size = 12, family = "Times New Roman"),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 12, family = "Times New Roman"),
    legend.text = element_text(size = 12, family = "Times New Roman"),

    legend.position = c(0.15, 0.8),  # Position legend inside plot

  ) +

  scale_shape_manual(
    values = c("Train Points" = 16),
    name = NULL,  # Remove legend title for shapes
    guide = NULL # Set order to 1, appears first
  ) +
  
  # Use equal spacing for x-axis labels and breaks
  scale_x_continuous(
    breaks = c(0.48, 1.92, 14.754, 22.131, 29.508),
    labels = c("0.48", "1.92", "14.75", "22.13", "29.51"),
    trans = custom_trans
   ) +
  # Add RMSE annotations with corresponding colors
  geom_text(data = rmse_results, 
            aes(x = 0.5, y = c(500, 450, 400),

# Read each sheet
data_mass_14_754 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass(14.754ng)")
data_mass_22_131 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass(22.131ng)")
data_mass_29_508 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass (29.508ng)")
data_mass_0_48 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass (0.48ng)")
data_mass_1_92 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass (1.92ng)")
data_mass_7_77 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass (7.77ng)")
data_mass_9_71 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass (9.71ng)")

# Add a column for the mass value to each dataset
data_mass_14_754$Mass <- 14.754
data_mass_22_131$Mass <- 22.131
data_mass_29_508$Mass <- 29.508
data_mass_0_48$Mass <- 0.48
data_mass_1_92$Mass <- 1.92
data_mass_7_77$Mass <- 7.77
data_mass_9_71$Mass <- 9.71

# Combine training and test datasets
combined_data <- bind_rows(data_mass_14_754, data_mass_22_131, data_mass_29_508, data_mass_0_48, data_mass_1_92)
test_data <- bind_rows(data_mass_7_77, data_mass_9_71)

# Prepare training and test datasets
train_data <- combined_data %>%
  rename(DrainVoltage = `Drain Voltage`)

test_data <- test_data %>%
  rename(DrainVoltage = `Drain Voltage`)

train_data_filtered <- train_data %>%
  filter(DrainVoltage %in% c(-4, -3, -2))

test_data_filtered <- test_data %>%
  filter(DrainVoltage %in% c(-4, -3, -2))

train_data_filtered <- train_data_filtered %>%
  mutate(diff1 = Control_Replication.1 - Exp_Replication.1,
         diff2 = Control_Replication.2 - Exp_Replication.2,
         diff3 = Control_Replication.3 - Exp_Replication.3)



test_data_filtered <- test_data_filtered %>%
  mutate(diff1 = Control_Replication.1 - Exp_Replication.1,
         diff2 = Control_Replication.2 - Exp_Replication.2,
         diff3 = Control_Replication.3 - Exp_Replication.3)


jitter_data <- train_data_filtered %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(diff1, diff2, diff3), names_to = "Replication", values_to = "Difference")

jitter_test_data<- test_data_filtered %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(diff1, diff2, diff3), names_to = "Replication", values_to = "Difference")



mean_sd_data <- train_data_filtered %>%
  group_by(Mass, DrainVoltage) %>%
  summarize(
    mean_diff = mean(c(diff1, diff2, diff3), na.rm = TRUE),
    SD_diff = sd(c(diff1, diff2, diff3), na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  distinct(Mass, DrainVoltage, mean_diff, SD_diff)


mean_sd_test_data <- test_data_filtered %>%
  group_by(Mass, DrainVoltage) %>%
  summarize(
    mean_diff = mean(c(diff1, diff2, diff3), na.rm = TRUE),
    SD_diff = sd(c(diff1, diff2, diff3), na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  distinct(Mass, DrainVoltage, mean_diff, SD_diff)


# Fit linear regression for each voltage
fits <- mean_sd_data %>%
  group_by(DrainVoltage) %>%
  do(fit = lm(mean_diff ~ Mass, data = .))

# Calculate fitted values and augment the data
fitted_data <- fits %>%
  do(augment(.$fit))

# Predict 'Difference' for test data using linear models fitted on training data
predicted_test_data <- test_data_filtered %>%
  group_by(DrainVoltage) %>%
  group_split() %>%
  map_df(~ {
    dv <- unique(.x$DrainVoltage)  # Extract unique Drain Voltage for each group
    # Fit a linear model on training data for the current DrainVoltage
    model <- lm(mean_diff ~ Mass, data = mean_sd_data %>% filter(DrainVoltage == dv))
    # Predict values for the test data
    predicted <- predict(model, newdata = data.frame(Mass = .x$Mass))
    # Return the dataframe containing the Mass, Actual, Predicted, and DrainVoltage
    data.frame(
      Mass = .x$Mass,
      Actual = rowMeans(.x %>% select(diff1, diff2, diff3), na.rm = TRUE),  # Average actual differences
      Predicted = predicted,
      DrainVoltage = dv
    )
  })


# Custom transformation for the x-axis
custom_trans <- trans_new(
  "custom",
  transform = function(x) {
    ifelse(
      x >= 0.48 & x <= 1.92, (x - 0.48) * 2.5 + 0.48,
      ifelse(
        x >= 7.77 & x <= 9.71, (x - 7.77) * 1.8+ 7.77,
        x
      )
    )
  },
  inverse = function(x) {
    ifelse(
      x >= 0.48 & x <= 1.92, (x - 0.48) / 1.5 + 0.48,
      ifelse(
        x >= 7.77 & x <= 9.71, (x - 7.77) / 1.1 + 7.77,
        x
      )
    )
  }
)

# Load fonts for Windows device
loadfonts(device = "win")

# Load data from the Excel file
file_path <- "Paper 2- Group 1 (1).xlsx"

# Read each sheet
data_mass_14_754 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass(14.754ng)")
data_mass_22_131 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass(22.131ng)")
data_mass_29_508 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass (29.508ng)")
data_mass_0_48 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass (0.48ng)")
data_mass_1_92 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass (1.92ng)")
data_mass_7_77 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass (7.77ng)")
data_mass_9_71 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass (9.71ng)")

  mutate(diff1 = Control_Replication.1 - Exp_Replication.1,
         diff2 = Control_Replication.2 - Exp_Replication.2,
         diff3 = Control_Replication.3 - Exp_Replication.3)



test_data_filtered <- test_data_filtered %>%

         diff3 = Control_Replication.3 - Exp_Replication.3)

# Custom transformation for the x-axis
custom_trans <- trans_new(
  "custom",
  transform = function(x) {
    ifelse(
      x >= 0.48 & x <= 1.92, (x - 0.48) * 2.5 + 0.48,
      ifelse(
        x >= 7.77 & x <= 9.71, (x - 7.77) * 1.8+ 7.77,
        x
      )
    )
  },
  inverse = function(x) {
    ifelse(
      x >= 0.48 & x <= 1.92, (x - 0.48) / 1.5 + 0.48,
      ifelse(
        x >= 7.77 & x <= 9.71, (x - 7.77) / 1.1 + 7.77,
        x
      )
    )
  }
)


# Define Langmuir adsorption model function
langmuir_model <- function(C, DeltaI_max, K) {
  DeltaI_max * (K * C / (1 + K * C))
}

# Fit Langmuir model for training data
fits <- mean_sd_data %>%
  group_by(DrainVoltage) %>%
  do({
    # Fit Langmuir model
    tryCatch({
      fit <- nlsLM(
        mean_diff ~ DeltaI_max * (K * Mass / (1 + K * Mass)),
        data = .,
        start = list(DeltaI_max = max(.$mean_diff, na.rm = TRUE), K = 1),
        control = nls.lm.control(maxiter = 100)
      )
      
      # Generate smooth predictions for the nonlinear curve
      Mass_seq <- seq(min(.$Mass), max(.$Mass), length.out = 100)
      Fitted <- langmuir_model(Mass_seq, coef(fit)["DeltaI_max"], coef(fit)["K"])
      
      # Return the fitted curve data
      data.frame(
        Mass = Mass_seq,
        Fitted = Fitted,
        DrainVoltage = unique(.$DrainVoltage)
      )
    }, error = function(e) {
      # Handle errors gracefully
      message("Error fitting Langmuir model for DrainVoltage = ", unique(.$DrainVoltage))
      return(data.frame(Mass = numeric(0), Fitted = numeric(0), DrainVoltage = unique(.$DrainVoltage)))
    })
  })

# Predict test data using Langmuir model
predicted_test_data <- test_data_filtered %>%
  group_by(DrainVoltage) %>%
  group_split() %>%
  map_df(~ {
    dv <- unique(.x$DrainVoltage)
    train_subset <- mean_sd_data %>% filter(DrainVoltage == dv)
    tryCatch({
      fit <- nlsLM(
        mean_diff ~ DeltaI_max * (K * Mass / (1 + K * Mass)),
        data = train_subset,
        start = list(DeltaI_max = max(train_subset$mean_diff, na.rm = TRUE), K = 1),
        control = nls.lm.control(maxiter = 100)
      )
      Predicted <- langmuir_model(.x$Mass, coef(fit)["DeltaI_max"], coef(fit)["K"])
      data.frame(
        Mass = .x$Mass,
        Actual = rowMeans(.x %>% select(diff1, diff2, diff3), na.rm = TRUE),
        Predicted = Predicted,
        DrainVoltage = dv
      )
    }, error = function(e) {
      # Handle errors gracefully
      message("Error predicting test data for DrainVoltage = ", dv)
      return(data.frame(Mass = .x$Mass, Actual = NA, Predicted = NA, DrainVoltage = dv))
    })
  })

  geom_line(
    data = mean_sd_data, 
    aes(x = Mass, y = mean_diff, group = DrainVoltage, color = DrainVoltage, linetype = "Actual Model"), 
    size = 0.8
  ) +
  
  # Define linetype mappings
  scale_linetype_manual(
    name = "Line Type",
    values = c("Fitted Model" = "dashed", "Actual Model" = "solid"),
    guide = guide_legend(order = 2)
  ) +
  
  # Labels and title
  labs(
    #title = "Langmuir Model",
    x = "DNA Mass (ng)",
    y = expression(bold(Differential~Current~(mu~A))),
    color = "Drain Voltage",
    shape = "Data Type"
  ) +
  
  # Formatting the plot
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(size = 18, face = "bold", family = "Times New Roman"),
    axis.text = element_text(size = 18, family = "Times New Roman"),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 18, face = "bold", family = "Times New Roman"),
    legend.text = element_text(size = 16, family = "Times New Roman"),
    legend.title =  element_text(size = 18, family = "Times New Roman"),
    legend.position = c(0.15, 0.75),  # Position legend inside plot
    legend.direction = "vertical",  # Arrange legend items vertically
    legend.spacing.y = unit(0.05, 'cm'),  # Reduce space between legend items
    legend.key.size = unit(0.5, 'lines'),  # Adjust legend key size
    panel.background = element_blank(), # Set background color to white
    plot.background = element_blank(), # Set plot background color to white
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(), # Remove major grid lines
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
    panel.border = element_rect(color = "black", fill = NA)

  # Custom color gradient for Drain Voltage
  scale_color_gradient(
    low = "#B8860B", 
    high = "navyblue",
    name = "Drain Voltage",
    breaks = c(-4, -3, -2),  # Specify legend values to display
    labels = c("-4.0", "-3.0", "-2.0"),  # Optional: formatted labels
    guide = guide_colorbar(order = 2)  # Set order to 2, appears after Data Type

  # Custom shapes for train, test, and predicted test data points
  scale_shape_manual(
    values = c("Train Points" = 16, "Test Points" = 17, "Predicted Test Points" = 18),
    name = NULL,  # Remove legend title for shapes
    guide = guide_legend(order = 1)  # Set order to 1, appears first

#####################################################
# Initialize RMSE results table
rmse_results <- tibble(
  DrainVoltage = numeric(),
  Model = character(),
  Dataset = character(),
  RMSE = numeric(),
  Normalized_RMSE = numeric()
)

target_voltages <- c(-4, -3, -2)

mean_sd_data_filtered <- mean_sd_data %>% filter(DrainVoltage %in% target_voltages)

mean_sd_test_data_filtered <- mean_sd_test_data %>% filter(DrainVoltage %in% target_voltages)


###############################
#RMSE
#####################################

# Iterate through each target voltage
for (voltage in target_voltages) {
  # Filter train and test data for the current voltage
  train_data <- mean_sd_data_filtered %>% filter(DrainVoltage == voltage)
  test_data <- mean_sd_test_data_filtered %>% filter(DrainVoltage == voltage)
  
  # Linear Model Predictions
  linear_fit <- lm(mean_diff ~ Mass, data = train_data)
  train_pred_linear <- predict(linear_fit, newdata = train_data)
  test_pred_linear <- predict(linear_fit, newdata = test_data)
  
  # Compute RMSE for Linear Model
  rmse_train_linear <- sqrt(mean((train_pred_linear - train_data$mean_diff)^2))
  rmse_test_linear <- sqrt(mean((test_pred_linear - test_data$mean_diff)^2))
  
  # Normalized RMSE
  norm_rmse_train_linear <- (rmse_train_linear / mean(train_data$mean_diff)) * 100
  norm_rmse_test_linear <- (rmse_test_linear / mean(test_data$mean_diff)) * 100
  
  # LOESS Model Predictions
  loess_fit <- loess(mean_diff ~ Mass, data = train_data, span = 6)
  train_pred_loess <- predict(loess_fit, newdata = train_data)
  test_pred_loess <- predict(loess_fit, newdata = test_data)
  
  # Compute RMSE for LOESS Model
  rmse_train_loess <- sqrt(mean((train_pred_loess - train_data$mean_diff)^2))
  rmse_test_loess <- sqrt(mean((test_pred_loess - test_data$mean_diff)^2))
  
  # Normalized RMSE
  norm_rmse_train_loess <- (rmse_train_loess / mean(train_data$mean_diff)) * 100
  norm_rmse_test_loess <- (rmse_test_loess / mean(test_data$mean_diff)) * 100
  
  # Langmuir Model Predictions
  langmuir_model <- function(C, DeltaI_max, K) {
    DeltaI_max * (K * C / (1 + K * C))
  }
  fit_langmuir <- nlsLM(
    mean_diff ~ langmuir_model(Mass, DeltaI_max, K),
    data = train_data,
    start = list(DeltaI_max = max(train_data$mean_diff, na.rm = TRUE), K = 0.1),
    control = nls.lm.control(maxiter = 500)
  )
  
  # Extract parameters for Langmuir model
  params_langmuir <- coef(fit_langmuir)
  DeltaI_max <- params_langmuir["DeltaI_max"]
  K <- params_langmuir["K"]
  
  # Langmuir predictions
  train_pred_langmuir <- langmuir_model(train_data$Mass, DeltaI_max, K)
  test_pred_langmuir <- langmuir_model(test_data$Mass, DeltaI_max, K)
  
  # Compute RMSE for Langmuir Model
  rmse_train_langmuir <- sqrt(mean((train_pred_langmuir - train_data$mean_diff)^2))
  rmse_test_langmuir <- sqrt(mean((test_pred_langmuir - test_data$mean_diff)^2))
  
  # Normalized RMSE
  norm_rmse_train_langmuir <- (rmse_train_langmuir / mean(train_data$mean_diff)) * 100
  norm_rmse_test_langmuir <- (rmse_test_langmuir / mean(test_data$mean_diff)) * 100
  
  # Append results to RMSE results table
  rmse_results <- rmse_results %>%
    add_row(DrainVoltage = voltage, Model = "Linear", Dataset = "Train", RMSE = rmse_train_linear, Normalized_RMSE = norm_rmse_train_linear) %>%
    add_row(DrainVoltage = voltage, Model = "Linear", Dataset = "Test", RMSE = rmse_test_linear, Normalized_RMSE = norm_rmse_test_linear) %>%
    add_row(DrainVoltage = voltage, Model = "LOESS", Dataset = "Train", RMSE = rmse_train_loess, Normalized_RMSE = norm_rmse_train_loess) %>%
    add_row(DrainVoltage = voltage, Model = "LOESS", Dataset = "Test", RMSE = rmse_test_loess, Normalized_RMSE = norm_rmse_test_loess) %>%
    add_row(DrainVoltage = voltage, Model = "Langmuir", Dataset = "Train", RMSE = rmse_train_langmuir, Normalized_RMSE = norm_rmse_train_langmuir) %>%
    add_row(DrainVoltage = voltage, Model = "Langmuir", Dataset = "Test", RMSE = rmse_test_langmuir, Normalized_RMSE = norm_rmse_test_langmuir)
}

data_mass_22_131 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass(22.131ng)")
data_mass_29_508 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass (29.508ng)")
data_mass_0_48 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass (0.48ng)")
data_mass_1_92 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass (1.92ng)")
data_mass_7_77 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass (7.77ng)")
data_mass_9_71 <- read_excel(file_path, sheet = "Mass (9.71ng)")

# Add a column for the mass value to each dataset
data_mass_14_754$Mass <- 14.754
data_mass_22_131$Mass <- 22.131
data_mass_29_508$Mass <- 29.508
data_mass_0_48$Mass <- 0.48
data_mass_1_92$Mass <- 1.92
data_mass_7_77$Mass <- 7.77
data_mass_9_71$Mass <- 9.71

# Combine training and test datasets
combined_data <- bind_rows(data_mass_14_754, data_mass_22_131, data_mass_29_508, data_mass_0_48, data_mass_1_92)
test_data <- bind_rows(data_mass_7_77, data_mass_9_71)

# Prepare training and test datasets
train_data <- combined_data %>%
  rename(DrainVoltage = `Drain Voltage`)

test_data <- test_data %>%
  rename(DrainVoltage = `Drain Voltage`)

train_data_filtered <- train_data %>%
  filter(DrainVoltage %in% c(-4, -3, -2))

test_data_filtered <- test_data %>%
  filter(DrainVoltage %in% c(-4, -3, -2))

train_data_filtered <- train_data_filtered %>%
  mutate(diff1 = Control_Replication.1 - Exp_Replication.1,
         diff2 = Control_Replication.2 - Exp_Replication.2,
         diff3 = Control_Replication.3 - Exp_Replication.3)



test_data_filtered <- test_data_filtered %>%
  mutate(diff1 = Control_Replication.1 - Exp_Replication.1,
         diff2 = Control_Replication.2 - Exp_Replication.2,
         diff3 = Control_Replication.3 - Exp_Replication.3)


jitter_data <- train_data_filtered %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(diff1, diff2, diff3), names_to = "Replication", values_to = "Difference")

jitter_test_data<- test_data_filtered %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(diff1, diff2, diff3), names_to = "Replication", values_to = "Difference")



mean_sd_data <- train_data_filtered %>%
  group_by(Mass, DrainVoltage) %>%
  summarize(
    mean_diff = mean(c(diff1, diff2, diff3), na.rm = TRUE),
    SD_diff = sd(c(diff1, diff2, diff3), na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  distinct(Mass, DrainVoltage, mean_diff, SD_diff)


mean_sd_test_data <- test_data_filtered %>%
  group_by(Mass, DrainVoltage) %>%
  summarize(
    mean_diff = mean(c(diff1, diff2, diff3), na.rm = TRUE),
    SD_diff = sd(c(diff1, diff2, diff3), na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  distinct(Mass, DrainVoltage, mean_diff, SD_diff)


# Fit LOESS model for each voltage
fits <- mean_sd_data %>%
  group_by(DrainVoltage) %>%
  do(data.frame(
    Mass = seq(min(.$Mass), max(.$Mass), length.out = 100),
    Fitted = predict(loess(mean_diff ~ Mass, data = ., span =0.6), newdata = data.frame(Mass = seq(min(.$Mass), max(.$Mass), length.out = 100)))
  ))


# Predict 'Difference' for test data using linear models fitted on training data
predicted_test_data <- test_data_filtered %>%
  group_by(DrainVoltage) %>%
  group_split() %>%
  map_df(~ {
    dv <- unique(.x$DrainVoltage)  # Extract unique Drain Voltage for each group
    # Fit a linear model on training data for the current DrainVoltage
    model <- loess(mean_diff ~ Mass, data = mean_sd_data %>% filter(DrainVoltage == dv),span =0.6)
    # Predict values for the test data
    predicted <- predict(model, newdata = data.frame(Mass = .x$Mass))
    # Return the dataframe containing the Mass, Actual, Predicted, and DrainVoltage
    data.frame(
      Mass = .x$Mass,
      Actual = rowMeans(.x %>% select(diff1, diff2, diff3), na.rm = TRUE),  # Average actual differences
      Predicted = predicted,
      DrainVoltage = dv
    )
  })


# Custom transformation for the x-axis
custom_trans <- trans_new(
  "custom",
  transform = function(x) {
    ifelse(
      x >= 0.48 & x <= 1.92, (x - 0.48) * 1.5 + 0.48,
      ifelse(
        x >= 7.77 & x <= 9.71, (x - 7.77) * 1.1 + 7.77,
        x
      )
    )
  },
  inverse = function(x) {
    ifelse(
      x >= 0.48 & x <= 1.92, (x - 0.48) / 1.5 + 0.48,
      ifelse(
        x >= 7.77 & x <= 9.71, (x - 7.77) / 1.1 + 7.77,
        x
      )
    )
  }
)

  filter(DrainVoltage %in% c(-4, -3, -2))

train_data_filtered <- train_data_filtered %>%
  mutate(diff1 = Control_Replication.1 - Exp_Replication.1,
         diff2 = Control_Replication.2 - Exp_Replication.2,
         diff3 = Control_Replication.3 - Exp_Replication.3)

test_data_filtered <- test_data_filtered %>%
  mutate(diff1 = Control_Replication.1 - Exp_Replication.1,
         diff2 = Control_Replication.2 - Exp_Replication.2,
         diff3 = Control_Replication.3 - Exp_Replication.3)

# Calculate mean and SD for training data
mean_sd_data <- train_data_filtered %>%
  group_by(Mass, DrainVoltage) %>%
  summarize(
    mean_diff = mean(c(diff1, diff2, diff3), na.rm = TRUE),
    SD_diff = sd(c(diff1, diff2, diff3), na.rm = TRUE)
  )

# Initialize an empty list to store results
rmse_results <- list()

# Loop over span values from 1 to 10
for (span_value in 1:10) {
  # Compute training RMSE
  train_rmse <- mean_sd_data %>%
    group_by(DrainVoltage) %>%
    do({
      model <- loess(mean_diff ~ Mass, data = ., span = span_value)
      predicted <- predict(model, newdata = .)
      residuals <- .$mean_diff - predicted
      rmse <- sqrt(mean(residuals^2, na.rm = TRUE))
      data.frame(
        DrainVoltage = unique(.$DrainVoltage),
        RMSE = rmse
      )
    })
  
  # Normalize RMSE for training data
  mean_diff_overall <- mean(mean_sd_data$mean_diff, na.rm = TRUE)
  train_rmse <- train_rmse %>%
    mutate(Normalized_RMSE = RMSE / mean_diff_overall * 100)
  
  # Compute test RMSE
  predicted_test_data <- test_data_filtered %>%
    group_by(DrainVoltage) %>%
    group_split() %>%
    map_df(~ {
      dv <- unique(.x$DrainVoltage)
      model <- loess(mean_diff ~ Mass, data = mean_sd_data %>% filter(DrainVoltage == dv), span = span_value)
      predicted <- predict(model, newdata = data.frame(Mass = .x$Mass))
      data.frame(
        Mass = .x$Mass,
        Actual = rowMeans(.x %>% select(diff1, diff2, diff3), na.rm = TRUE),
        Predicted = predicted,
        DrainVoltage = dv
      )
    })
  
  test_rmse <- predicted_test_data %>%
    group_by(DrainVoltage) %>%
    summarize(
      RMSE = sqrt(mean((Actual - Predicted)^2, na.rm = TRUE))
    ) %>%
    mutate(Normalized_RMSE = RMSE / mean_diff_overall * 100)
  
  # Combine results for this span value
  train_rmse <- train_rmse %>% mutate(Dataset = "Train", Span = span_value)
  test_rmse <- test_rmse %>% mutate(Dataset = "Test", Span = span_value)
  
  # Add to results list
  rmse_results[[span_value]] <- bind_rows(train_rmse, test_rmse)
}

# Combine all results into a single data frame
rmse_results_df <- bind_rows(rmse_results)

# Aggregate RMSE values by computing the mean across all drain voltages for each span
mean_rmse_results <- rmse_results_df %>%
  group_by(Span, Dataset) %>%
  summarize(Mean_Normalized_RMSE = mean(Normalized_RMSE, na.rm = TRUE), .groups = "drop")

# Plot the mean RMSE for Train and Test datasets
mean_rmse_plot <- ggplot(mean_rmse_results, aes(x = Span, y = Mean_Normalized_RMSE, color = Dataset, group = Dataset)) +
  geom_line(size = 1) +
  geom_point(size = 3) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("Train" = "#B8860B", "Test" = "navyblue")) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(1, 10, by = 1), limits = c(1, 10)) + 
  labs(
    x = "Span",
    y = "Mean RMSE (%)"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    axis.text = element_text(size = 12, family = "Times New Roman"),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 12, family = "Times New Roman"),
    legend.text = element_text(size = 12, family = "Times New Roman"),
    legend.title = element_text(size = 12, family = "Times New Roman"),
    legend.position = c(0.8, 0.75),  # Position legend inside plot
    legend.direction = "vertical",  # Arrange legend items vertically
    legend.spacing.y = unit(0.05, 'cm'),  # Reduce space between legend items
    legend.key.size = unit(0.5, 'lines'),  # Adjust legend key size
    panel.background = element_blank(), # Set background color to white
    plot.background = element_blank(), # Set plot background color to white
    panel.grid.major = element_blank(), # Remove major grid lines
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
    panel.border = element_rect(color = "black", fill = NA)
  )

# Fit Langmuir model to estimate K and Imax
langmuir_parameters <- mean_sd_data %>%
  group_by(DrainVoltage) %>%
  do({
    tryCatch({
      # Fit Langmuir adsorption model
      fit <- nlsLM(
        mean_diff ~ DeltaI_max * (K * Mass / (1 + K * Mass)),
        data = .,
        start = list(DeltaI_max = max(.$mean_diff, na.rm = TRUE), K = 1),
        control = nls.lm.control(maxiter = 100)
      )
      
      # Extract coefficients for K and Imax
      params <- coef(fit)
      data.frame(
        DrainVoltage = unique(.$DrainVoltage),
        K = params["K"],
        DeltaI_max = params["DeltaI_max"]
      )
    }, error = function(e) {
      # Handle errors gracefully
      message("Error fitting Langmuir model for DrainVoltage = ", unique(.$DrainVoltage))
      return(data.frame(DrainVoltage = unique(.$DrainVoltage), K = NA, DeltaI_max = NA))
    })
  })

# Display the estimated parameters
print(langmuir_parameters)

mean_sd_data_filtered <- mean_sd_data %>% filter(DrainVoltage %in% target_voltages)

###############################
#RMSE

# Iterate through each target voltage
for (voltage in target_voltages) {
  # Filter train and test data for the current voltage
  train_data <- mean_sd_data_filtered %>% filter(DrainVoltage == voltage)
  test_data <- mean_sd_test_data_filtered %>% filter(DrainVoltage == voltage)
  
  # Linear Model Predictions
  linear_fit <- lm(mean_diff ~ Mass, data = train_data)
  train_pred_linear <- predict(linear_fit, newdata = train_data)
  test_pred_linear <- predict(linear_fit, newdata = test_data)
  
  # Compute RMSE for Linear Model
  rmse_train_linear <- sqrt(mean((train_pred_linear - train_data$mean_diff)^2))
  rmse_test_linear <- sqrt(mean((test_pred_linear - test_data$mean_diff)^2))
  
  # Normalized RMSE
  norm_rmse_train_linear <- (rmse_train_linear / mean(train_data$mean_diff)) * 100
  norm_rmse_test_linear <- (rmse_test_linear / mean(test_data$mean_diff)) * 100
  
  # LOESS Model Predictions
  loess_fit <- loess(mean_diff ~ Mass, data = train_data, span = 6)
  train_pred_loess <- predict(loess_fit, newdata = train_data)
  test_pred_loess <- predict(loess_fit, newdata = test_data)
  
  # Compute RMSE for LOESS Model
  rmse_train_loess <- sqrt(mean((train_pred_loess - train_data$mean_diff)^2))
  rmse_test_loess <- sqrt(mean((test_pred_loess - test_data$mean_diff)^2))
  
  # Normalized RMSE
  norm_rmse_train_loess <- (rmse_train_loess / mean(train_data$mean_diff)) * 100
  norm_rmse_test_loess <- (rmse_test_loess / mean(test_data$mean_diff)) * 100
  
  # Langmuir Model Predictions
  langmuir_model <- function(C, DeltaI_max, K) {
    DeltaI_max * (K * C / (1 + K * C))
  }
  fit_langmuir <- nlsLM(
    mean_diff ~ langmuir_model(Mass, DeltaI_max, K),
    data = train_data,
    start = list(DeltaI_max = max(train_data$mean_diff, na.rm = TRUE), K = 0.1),
    control = nls.lm.control(maxiter = 500)
  )
  
  # Extract parameters for Langmuir model
  params_langmuir <- coef(fit_langmuir)
  DeltaI_max <- params_langmuir["DeltaI_max"]
  K <- params_langmuir["K"]
  
  # Langmuir predictions
  train_pred_langmuir <- langmuir_model(train_data$Mass, DeltaI_max, K)
  test_pred_langmuir <- langmuir_model(test_data$Mass, DeltaI_max, K)
  
  # Compute RMSE for Langmuir Model
  rmse_train_langmuir <- sqrt(mean((train_pred_langmuir - train_data$mean_diff)^2))
  rmse_test_langmuir <- sqrt(mean((test_pred_langmuir - test_data$mean_diff)^2))
  
  # Normalized RMSE
  norm_rmse_train_langmuir <- (rmse_train_langmuir / mean(train_data$mean_diff)) * 100
  norm_rmse_test_langmuir <- (rmse_test_langmuir / mean(test_data$mean_diff)) * 100
  
  # Append results to RMSE results table
  rmse_results <- rmse_results %>%
    add_row(DrainVoltage = voltage, Model = "Linear", Dataset = "Train", RMSE = rmse_train_linear, Normalized_RMSE = norm_rmse_train_linear) %>%
    add_row(DrainVoltage = voltage, Model = "Linear", Dataset = "Test", RMSE = rmse_test_linear, Normalized_RMSE = norm_rmse_test_linear) %>%
    add_row(DrainVoltage = voltage, Model = "LOESS", Dataset = "Train", RMSE = rmse_train_loess, Normalized_RMSE = norm_rmse_train_loess) %>%
    add_row(DrainVoltage = voltage, Model = "LOESS", Dataset = "Test", RMSE = rmse_test_loess, Normalized_RMSE = norm_rmse_test_loess) %>%
    add_row(DrainVoltage = voltage, Model = "Langmuir", Dataset = "Train", RMSE = rmse_train_langmuir, Normalized_RMSE = norm_rmse_train_langmuir) %>%
    add_row(DrainVoltage = voltage, Model = "Langmuir", Dataset = "Test", RMSE = rmse_test_langmuir, Normalized_RMSE = norm_rmse_test_langmuir)
}

1.12 TableS4-5

# Filter for specific voltages (-4, -3, -2)
target_voltages <- c(-4, -3, -2)

# Define constants
z <- 1.645  # For 95% confidence level

# Initialize an empty results dataframe
lod_results <- data.frame(
  DrainVoltage = numeric(),
  LoB = numeric(),
  LOD_Linear = numeric(),
  Slope_Linear = numeric(),
  LOD_LOESS = numeric(),
  Slope_LOESS = numeric(),
  LOD_Langmuir = numeric(),
  Slope_Langmuir = numeric()
)

# Filter the data for target voltages
mean_sd_data_filtered <- mean_sd_data %>% filter(DrainVoltage %in% target_voltages)

# Iterate through each target voltage
for (voltage in target_voltages) {
  # Filter data for the current voltage
  voltage_data <- mean_sd_data_filtered %>% filter(DrainVoltage == voltage)
  
  # Filter low-concentration data (Mass = 0.48 ng)
  low_conc_data <- voltage_data %>% filter(Mass == 0.48)
  
  # Compute mean and standard deviation of the blank signal
  sd <- low_conc_data$SD_diff
  
  
  # Linear model slope
  linear_fit <- lm(mean_diff ~ Mass, data = voltage_data)
  slope_linear <- coef(linear_fit)["Mass"]
  lod_linear <- 3.3 * sd / slope_linear
  
  # LOESS slope at Mass = 0.48
  loess_fit <- loess(mean_diff ~ Mass, data = voltage_data, span = 6)
  mass_small_range <- seq(0.48, 1.0, length.out = 50)
  fitted_values_small <- predict(loess_fit, newdata = data.frame(Mass = mass_small_range))
  slope_loess <- gradient(fitted_values_small, mass_small_range)[1] # Derivative at Mass = 0.48
  lod_loess <- 3.3 * sd/ slope_loess
  
  # Langmuir model slope
  langmuir_model <- function(C, DeltaI_max, K) {
    DeltaI_max * (K * C / (1 + K * C))
  }
  
  # Fit the Langmuir model for the current voltage
  fit_langmuir <- nlsLM(
    mean_diff ~ langmuir_model(Mass, DeltaI_max, K),
    data = voltage_data,
    start = list(DeltaI_max = max(voltage_data$mean_diff, na.rm = TRUE), K = 1),
    control = nls.lm.control(maxiter = 500)
  )
  
  # Extract fitted parameters
  params_langmuir <- coef(fit_langmuir)
  DeltaI_max <- params_langmuir["DeltaI_max"]
  K <- params_langmuir["K"]
  
  # Function to calculate slope (derivative) for the Langmuir model
  langmuir_slope <- function(C, DeltaI_max, K) {
    DeltaI_max * (K / ((1 + K * C)^2))
  }
  
  # Calculate slope at Mass = 0.48
  slope_langmuir <- langmuir_slope(0.48, DeltaI_max, K)
  lod_langmuir <- 3.3 * sd / slope_langmuir
  
  # Store results
  lod_results <- lod_results %>%
    add_row(
      DrainVoltage = voltage,
      LOD_Linear = lod_linear,
      Slope_Linear = slope_linear,
      LOD_LOESS = lod_loess,
      Slope_LOESS = slope_loess,
      LOD_Langmuir = lod_langmuir,
      Slope_Langmuir = slope_langmuir
    )
}

# Print the results
print(lod_results)
